In England, in the seven days to 10 February, there were 353,632 new confirmed cases (625.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 03 February, there were 513,237 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 31% (159,605 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 15 February is 15,684,719 (27,736 cases per 100,000 population).
